Reference

All functions

drop_extramergevars()

Clean up data by dropping variables systematically

gee_datapull()

Pull spatial data from google earth engine (GEE) for a given region on any feature in the google earth engine database

gee_downloadimage()

Pull Large Images from Google Earth Engine's Image Collections for further extraction

gee_pullbigdata()

Another pulling function for pulling Google Earth Engine data for larger maps

gee_pullimage()

Pull Images from Google Earth Engine

gengrid()

Polygonize a raster and compute zonal statistics at polygon and full shape-file level

gengrid2()

Another function to create a gridified shapefile and extract a raster if specified

hdx_pull()

Check and pull data from Humanitarian Data Exchange

mult_gengrid()

Polygonize multiple rasters (TIFs) and compute zonal statistics at polygon and full shape-file level

osm_cleanprocess()

This function does simple cleaning of the OSM data for lines, multipolygons and points

osm_datapull()

This function pulls specific layer data (lines, multipolygons and points) from the Open Street Maps for countries or regions

osm_processlines()

This function creates indicators from OSM lines data in preparation for survey to survey imputation analysis

osm_processmp()

This function computes the number of points for the multipolygon data based on selected features

osm_processpoints()

This function cleans up OSM lines data in preparation for survey to survey imputation analysis

parallel_extract()

Extract group of rasters into the same grid

saeplus_addbenchmark()

A simple function to include benchmarked results to preferred file

saeplus_calibratepovrate()

This function benchmarks the poverty rates to match survey estimates

saeplus_checkshpfiles()

Check for inconsistencies in the administrative boundaries shapefile

saeplus_conssummary()

Compute Outcome Variable Summary Statistics

saeplus_dropchars()

Remove non-numeric characters

saeplus_dummify()

Create dummy variables

saeplus_gencensus()

Create a synthetic census

saeplus_hhestpoly()

Compute the geospatial grid level estimates

saeplus_modelsubarea()

Small Estimation of a Sub Area Level Model

saeplus_modelunitlevel()

Estimate the unit level model

saeplus_ordernormpl()

Compute National Poverty Line

saeplus_prepdata()

Prepare geospatial data for small area estimation

saeplus_regtable()

Create report ready tables from EBP output

saeplus_selectmodel()

Select Model for Small Area Estimation

wpopbuilding_pull()

Automate the process of pulling building data from the World Pop website

wpopbuilding_vcheck()

This function returns a datatable of all available versions of World Pop raster building data in each country with available
